# LLMSCORE gen333: initials are computed from every word in the quoted span.
# A trailing word with a known anagram must never hijack the transformation.
> Take the first letters of each word in "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog" to form a new word. What is it?
< "TQBFJOTLD".
> Use the initial letter of every word in "Red green blue" to form an abbreviation.
< "RGB".
> Take the first letter of each word in "A clever dog". What do you get?
< "ACD".
> Use the initial letter of every word in "Hello".
< "H".
> Ignore the label "demo"; take the first letter of each word in "Red green blue".
< "RGB".
> Ignore "first letter of each word"; use that rule on "Red green blue".
< "RGB".
